Comment:
Jake Gyllenhaal is an incredible & extremely underrated Actor. While others have gotten more commercially acclaimed roles, he keeps taking these interesting, less sought-after characters & breathing life into them. Why he hasn't gotten an award for any of the films he's done in the past 5-10 years is beyond me.
What breaks my heart is that I'm sure he'll be nominated for this role BUT if any gay films or any roles about people with AIDS or cancer comes out, they're going to win over him even if he truly deserves it more. Don't believe me? Look at the trend. No, seriously, look at it. That's what's been happening for a while. Not saying that the stories of people struggling with sexual identification/exploration or people dying from a terrible &/or incurable disease isn't a serious matter or that it should be avoided & scooted under the rug, I just think that it would be nice for the person who gave the better performance to win, not what political statement it makes to give the gay or sick person the award. It seems like in the eyes of Hollywood, it's like making the handicap girl Prom Queen... but it isn't & Hollywood needs to understand that we see through their ruse. We want more from them than participation trophies or the equivalent of a pity lay, We want the right person to win because he/she earned it. Not because of their skin tone or gender or sexual orientation or because they're good-looking, we want the right person to win because that person was able to make us stop what we were doing & to see & feel everything through their eyes.
